The paper discusses the development of techniques for validating the results computed by Boolean optimizers, which are widely used in various application domains. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category, as Boolean optimization is a common problem in AI. Additionally, the paper involves iterative calls to an NP oracle, which is a common technique in the Design and Analysis of Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also discusses the validation of both satisfiable and unsatisfiable answers, which suggests that it could belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper could belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category, as Boolean optimization is often used in programming language design and optimization. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of the proposed method on overall performance, which suggests that it could belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
